<subSubSection id="7E59DB2C88B6E324369F4CD5BDCF16AD" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="3D65664B15CB95A02C170A220E9D29A4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32C5350BD062E2BB60677EC31AA4EE58" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Endemic to Sutherland, Scotland, where it is known from four sites in Sutherland: in a gorge and on a burn side near Rhiconich; on a burn side in Coire 
<normalizedToken id="EA4C32489172B356BEA1D776BFAA3AAF" originalValue="Dùail">Duail</normalizedToken>
, Foinaven; and on rocks at Creag na h-Uidhe (
<figureCitation id="7FA3B953CAA853FB5596B3AA3CBEE5BD" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Hieracium maccoshiana in Scotland." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/9873" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The status of plants from Ben Loyal remains to be clarified when it has been refound in the field
<pageBreakToken id="4BEFDCAB4AAD49B4A67BBD70DFEF2460" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" start="start">.</pageBreakToken>
</paragraph>
